pc:TextEquiv.pc:Unicode: 1. Home, dear home, we never can forget,
Bless'd by care, or pierced by grief,
Friends, dear friends, we often there have met,
Home has af-ford-ed us a sweet re - lief.
2. Lured by gain we seek a foreign shore, Worn and weary keep the golden ore; Still our yearning hearts demand Rest in the homestead in our native land.
3. On the gilded page of earthly fame Some may pant to register their name; Round our names no wreath may be,
But you may read them on the old home tree.
Ten-der memories round thee twine, Like the ivy green round the pine; Over land and sea we may roam, Still will we cherish thee our own dear home.
